					<description><![CDATA[Love this post, and I agree with everything. Would love to see an expansion of the other side of the equation: creating environments that amplify positive behaviours. Making unhealthy food inaccessible is great, and the flip side is to stock your home with appealing and easily made healthy treats. Personally, my trick is to really focus on being strong in the grocery store since that is the genesis of most foods that find their way into my home. Don&#039;t ever shop hungry and plan and commit to being ruthless for that one hour and the rest of the week is so much easier when you block that crap from entering your home.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Love this post, and I agree with everything. Would love to see an expansion of the other side of the equation: creating environments that amplify positive behaviours. Making unhealthy food inaccessible is great, and the flip side is to stock your home with appealing and easily made healthy treats. Personally, my trick is to really focus on being strong in the grocery store since that is the genesis of most foods that find their way into my home. Don&#8217;t ever shop hungry and plan and commit to being ruthless for that one hour and the rest of the week is so much easier when you block that crap from entering your home.</p>
