					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.vercel.app/lewins-equation#comment-11386&quot;&gt;Tony Barton&lt;/a&gt;.

Hey Steffen

I wanted to apologise. Yesterday I was a little taken a back with your comments. 

I just read them again and am getting what you&#039;re saying. Your advice is so foreign that I didn&#039;t get it at first. 

In hindsight willpower has never been present in any of the major changes that I have made.  The keys for me have been goal setting, visualisation, planning, preparation, implementation and assessment.  

However, the biggest piece by far is &quot;mindfulness&quot;. Paying attention in the moment, moment by moment, as if your life depended on it.

Thanks for making the effort to comment. You changed how I think. Good on you.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.vercel.app/lewins-equation#comment-11386">Tony Barton</a>.</p>
<p>Hey Steffen</p>
<p>I wanted to apologise. Yesterday I was a little taken a back with your comments. </p>
<p>I just read them again and am getting what you&#8217;re saying. Your advice is so foreign that I didn&#8217;t get it at first. </p>
<p>In hindsight willpower has never been present in any of the major changes that I have made.  The keys for me have been goal setting, visualisation, planning, preparation, implementation and assessment.  </p>
<p>However, the biggest piece by far is &#8220;mindfulness&#8221;. Paying attention in the moment, moment by moment, as if your life depended on it.</p>
<p>Thanks for making the effort to comment. You changed how I think. Good on you.</p>
